18:56.633 --> 18:57.895
They still didn't possess it.

18:58.816 --> 19:03.763
In the midst of fear, they forgot whose they were, and they forgot who spoke the command.

19:04.444 --> 19:05.986
Can I have an honesty moment with you guys?

19:06.527 --> 19:07.028
Is that okay?

19:07.248 --> 19:08.690
People I can trust in this room?

19:09.026 --> 19:09.507
Amen.

19:10.047 --> 19:18.357
So in my role as a training educational psychologist, part of what I might do is deliver training to school staff or different educational staff.

19:18.417 --> 19:21.201
And there was a time where I was delivering some staff training.

19:22.222 --> 19:29.971
And then there was a lot of negative reports coming out about kind of children and young people today, kind of what they're not, what they lack, what they aren't able to do.

19:30.813 --> 19:36.279
And without realizing it, my perspective began to shift and I started to sound more like the 10th than the two.

19:36.319 --> 19:38.642
Echoing a negative report.

19:39.650 --> 19:41.632
You see, belief in God's power was still there.

19:41.652 --> 19:44.555
The faith that God can move was still there.

19:44.575 --> 19:45.636
It hadn't disappeared.

19:46.317 --> 19:49.740
But fear had slowly began to shape my expectations.

19:51.081 --> 19:54.345
And in his kindness, the Lord brought conviction in the same day.

19:54.405 --> 19:58.569
Because how many of you know that bad reports don't just affect what we say.

19:58.629 --> 20:01.251
They shape what we begin to believe as possible.

20:02.833 --> 20:07.858
And perhaps that feels similar and familiar to some of us in this room or online.

20:07.970 --> 20:13.435
when what we see and what we hear or what we face, quietly lowers our expectations of what God can do.

20:14.316 --> 20:19.842
Maybe like me, you've looked at situations around you and spoken to feet while God had already declared victory.

20:19.882 --> 20:24.907
And I wanted to read something from my journal for you guys.

20:24.967 --> 20:34.236
