21:09.336 --> 21:10.678
The page is going to come to me.

21:10.698 --> 21:14.063
Do you know what I mean?

21:16.186 --> 21:16.447
Okay.

21:16.467 --> 21:16.707
Amen.

21:16.968 --> 21:17.408
Amen.

21:17.669 --> 21:19.692
And if it doesn't, I'll just speak from my heart.

21:20.052 --> 21:20.333
Okay.

21:20.593 --> 21:21.114
It's not there.

21:21.214 --> 21:29.466
So what I wrote about was that this generation warrants a negative report, right?

21:29.526 --> 21:32.210
What we see in our physical reality

21:32.706 --> 21:34.408
is perhaps not what we'd want to see.

21:34.468 --> 21:37.932
We're so caught up in, you know, what they're not doing.

21:37.952 --> 21:43.258
And actually, what the Lord reminded me of was that he has already told us what he's doing in this generation.

21:43.278 --> 21:50.846
In Acts it says, he will pour out his spirit upon all flesh, that our sons and daughters will begin to prophesy, that old men will dream dreams.

21:51.907 --> 21:52.828
And we've heard it, haven't we?

21:52.848 --> 21:54.610
The word revival over and over again.

21:54.650 --> 21:56.953
And it was a challenge of whether or not I really believed that.

21:57.794 --> 22:01.618
And actually, what the 10 did actually caused the disruption in the mission.

22:01.954 --> 22:04.777
that the Israelites were delayed for 40 years of wandering.

22:04.817 --> 22:07.619
But then Joshua and Caleb led them into the promised land.

22:08.020 --> 22:12.904
And in Joshua 1, 3, it says, wherever you place your foot is the land I have given you.

22:12.944 --> 22:17.529
Wherever you place your foot is the land God has given you.

22:18.550 --> 22:25.837
So don't worry about what the world reports, but let's be people who take ground with authority and do not shrink back.

22:25.917 --> 22:26.297
Amen.

22:27.458 --> 22:27.879
Amen.

22:29.980 --> 22:31.602
And sitting with that reminder,

22:32.002 --> 22:45.401
I was reminded of the younger me who I mentioned earlier, the one who couldn't ignore justice, the one who stepped into situations others walked past, the one who believed righteousness and truth mattered, even when silence would have been much easier.

22:45.421 --> 22:47.785
That fire had not disappeared.

22:47.805 --> 22:49.587
It had been placed there by God.

22:50.248 --> 22:55.716
And in that moment, something arose in my spirit to encourage us with today, not on our watch.

22:57.098 --> 22:59.762
Not on our watch will this generation be written off.

23:00.930 --> 23:03.834
Not on our watch will fear dictate what God can do.

23:03.855 --> 23:09.804
Not on our watch will we agree with a bad report when God had already spoken a better word.

23:11.166 --> 23:14.591
Church, let's not allow the noise of this well to distort the truth.

23:15.012 --> 23:23.645
You are called, soul church, you are called, you are chosen, and you are the beloved of the most high God.

23:23.685 --> 23:29.394
Therefore nothing and nobody can come against you on mission.

23:30.178 --> 23:31.159
Everyone say nothing.

23:31.199 --> 23:36.887
And now nobody can come against you on mission.

23:37.388 --> 23:42.656
Romans 8, 31 says this, what then shall we say in response to these things?

23:43.116 --> 23:46.681
If God is for us, who can be against us?

23:46.962 --> 23:47.402
Amen.

23:47.462 --> 23:49.766
And we know the answer to that scripture, right?

23:49.886 --> 23:51.648
Who can be against us?

23:52.650 --> 23:55.073
Nobody and nothing.

23:55.173 --> 23:56.695
That's what the word of God says.

23:57.476 --> 23:58.578
Don't shrink back.

23:59.682 --> 24:00.804
Don't shrink back.

24:01.284 --> 24:02.506
Okay, he's ready for point number three.

24:03.708 --> 24:04.309
Okay, good.

24:04.790 --> 24:08.756
Point number three, faith shifts perspectives.

24:10.017 --> 24:12.261
Same situation, different vision.

24:13.262 --> 24:15.786
Same situation, different vision.

24:15.826 --> 24:25.701
In numbers 13, 30 it says, then Caleb silenced the people before Moses and said, we should go up and take possession of the land, but we can certainly do it.

24:26.863 --> 24:29.106
We can certainly do it so church,

24:30.306 --> 24:45.384
And in Numbers 14, verses six to nine, it says, Joshua, son of nine and Caleb, son of Jeffinere, who were among those who had explored the land, tore their clothes and said to the entire Israelite assembly, the land be passed through and explored is exceedingly good.

24:45.925 --> 24:52.793
If the Lord is pleased with us, he will lead us into that land, a land flowing with milk and honey and will give it to us.

24:53.394 --> 25:00.242
Only do not rebel against the Lord and do not be afraid of the people of the land because we will devour them

25:01.794 --> 25:03.856
Do not be afraid of the people of the land.

25:04.177 --> 25:08.162
Do not be afraid of the enemy of Islam because the battle has already been won.

25:08.202 --> 25:10.544
The battle has already been won.

25:10.564 --> 25:15.450
And it goes on to say, their protection is gone, but the Lord is with us.

25:16.071 --> 25:17.793
Do not be afraid of them, amen?

25:19.295 --> 25:24.861
Caleb and Joshua were only two men amongst the majority, just two men.

25:24.881 --> 25:28.786
They could have felt outnumbered, but they chose to speak up.

25:29.186 --> 25:32.410
And in silence in these 10 men, they reinstated the mission.

25:33.171 --> 25:34.793
Come on guys, we can do this.

25:35.453 --> 25:36.374
It is possible.

25:36.434 --> 25:39.438
They didn't deny the giants.

25:40.179 --> 25:41.801
They just refused to magnify them.

25:41.841 --> 25:45.946
They just refused to magnify them.

25:47.748 --> 25:50.150
So I'm not saying the giants in your life aren't real.

25:50.911 --> 25:52.573
I have real giants too, believe me.

25:53.174 --> 25:56.658
But it's not, but it's what we choose to magnify that matters most.

25:57.730 --> 26:04.977
Being on mission doesn't mean we ignore the realities around us, but what it does do is uphold a word that is spoken in truth.

26:06.519 --> 26:09.622
I wonder what giant has been speaking louder than God's mission in your life.

26:12.044 --> 26:14.647
I wonder what giants need to silence in this room today.

26:14.707 --> 26:26.098
And for those of you watching online, you see with the 10 in numbers 13 and 33, the 10 leaders said, we seemed like grasshoppers in our own eyes.

26:27.010 --> 26:28.392
This is the place they'd got to.

26:28.452 --> 26:30.175
They weren't small.

26:30.195 --> 26:31.117
They were leaders.

26:31.197 --> 26:34.102
They were leaders of the Israelites, the 12 tribes.

26:34.182 --> 26:36.325
And yet, they diminished themselves.

26:36.345 --> 26:39.531
They shrunk back and they were referring to themselves as grasshoppers.

26:40.753 --> 26:42.515
We seemed like grasshoppers.

26:43.798 --> 26:44.699
They shrank back.

26:45.701 --> 26:47.564
And their fear didn't just remain personal.

26:47.584 --> 26:48.445
It didn't stop there.

26:49.026 --> 26:53.874
They spread that bad report amongst an entire nation of people.

26:54.946 --> 27:00.834
And what began as fear turned into unbelief that disrupted the mission of an entire nation.

27:00.894 --> 27:09.846
What began as someone's personal fear led to unbelief of an entire nation.

27:09.906 --> 27:11.949
What are your words doing?

27:14.232 --> 27:15.474
What are your words doing?

27:16.415 --> 27:20.521
Are they declaring faith or proclaiming fear to those closest to you?

27:22.684 --> 27:24.466
Oh, we're only one church.

27:25.282 --> 27:27.065
I'm only new to this, I'm a new Christian.

27:27.125 --> 27:32.853
I'm the only Christian in my family, the only Christian in my workplace, in my school.

27:35.017 --> 27:36.499
But can I tell you something, Church?

27:37.821 --> 27:38.161
Can I?

27:40.485 --> 27:42.127
God has never been limited by numbers.

27:43.429 --> 27:44.211
Only unbelief.

27:46.474 --> 27:47.916
So maybe you are the only one.

27:47.936 --> 27:51.762
And that's okay, because God can use one person

27:52.194 --> 27:55.259
but actually when we have unbelief, it disrupts what God can do.

27:56.520 --> 27:58.243
So church do not shrink back.

27:59.304 --> 28:02.529
Let's be a people that when God speaks, we move.

28:03.210 --> 28:05.654
When God speaks, we move.

28:06.074 --> 28:12.965
When God speaks, amen, and things begin to shift and to happen in our lives for the glory of God.

28:14.307 --> 28:18.072
Caleb and Joshua were just two men, but they knew who they belonged to.

28:18.132 --> 28:22.098
They said the land was exceedingly good.

28:22.562 --> 28:23.583
The Lord will lead us.

28:25.045 --> 28:27.028
The Lord will give it to us.

28:27.488 --> 28:28.570
He will be with us.

28:29.771 --> 28:32.295
In the face of fear, they chose to speak faith.

28:33.596 --> 28:41.687
I want to encourage some of you in this room today, you're spending too long on the bad report, not on my watch, not on our watch, enough's enough.

28:41.727 --> 28:44.951
The bad report, okay, that might be the reality, but who do we serve?

28:46.092 --> 28:46.513
Amen.

28:46.933 --> 28:50.578
So you need to start confessing faith in the face of fear.

28:51.426 --> 28:57.853
Being on mission isn't just a new slogan for the year or a wristband that we wear, so people can go, well, what's that?

28:57.913 --> 28:59.215
No, that's not just what it means.

29:01.337 --> 29:03.059
It's a God or deigned mission.

29:03.079 --> 29:05.282
A God or deigned mission.

29:05.362 --> 29:08.045
That means we don't have to be afraid of the giants.

29:08.786 --> 29:10.988
We don't have to listen to the voices of fear.

29:11.569 --> 29:16.114
We don't have to shrink back because the Lord of Heaven's armies goes before us.

29:16.258 --> 29:21.363
I love how the psalmist puts it in Psalm 24, verse 18. Who is this king of glory?

29:21.403 --> 29:23.906
The Lord strong and mighty.

29:23.946 --> 29:26.028
The Lord mighty in battle.

29:26.568 --> 29:27.629
That's the God we serve.

29:27.649 --> 29:28.851
We sung about it this morning.

29:29.191 --> 29:30.252
His fighting for us.

29:30.292 --> 29:31.894
He's won every single battle.

29:31.914 --> 29:33.876
Don't shrink back.

29:35.878 --> 29:37.199
Don't shrink back, so church.

29:37.780 --> 29:39.381
And finally, point number four.

29:41.343 --> 29:44.306
Shrinking back has eternal consequences.

29:44.770 --> 29:47.494
but so does obedience.

29:47.514 --> 29:52.040
Shrinking back has eternal consequences, but so does obedience.

29:52.100 --> 29:55.244
I want you to see something in Numbers 14, verses 22 to 23.

29:56.105 --> 29:59.449
And it's one of those scriptures that you read and you're like, oh, that's not great.

29:59.469 --> 30:02.093
But this is what God said about the 10.

30:02.954 --> 30:09.202
Not one of those who saw my glory and the signs I performed in Egypt and in the wilderness, but who

30:09.314 --> 30:11.576
It disobeyed me and tested me ten times.

30:12.077 --> 30:16.401
Not one of them will ever see the land I promised on over to their ancestors.

30:17.262 --> 30:18.022
Not one of them.

30:18.062 --> 30:20.805
No one has treated me with contempt.

30:20.865 --> 30:24.048
No one who has treated me with contempt will ever see it.

30:27.011 --> 30:31.775
See, delay didn't cancel the promise or the mission, but it did change who entered into it.

30:33.697 --> 30:35.339
It did change who entered into it.

30:36.160 --> 30:38.642
Shrinking back costs to tend the promise.

30:39.298 --> 30:43.184
And God can't fulfill a promise amongst the people who did not move with the mission.

30:45.046 --> 30:47.490
But I don't want to dwell here because look at verse 24.

30:49.352 --> 30:59.146
But because my servant Caleb has a different spirit and follows me wholeheartedly, I will bring him into the land he went to and his descendants will inherit it.

31:00.228 --> 31:01.169
How beautiful is that?

31:01.209 --> 31:07.218
You see, God doesn't say Caleb was louder or more confident or stronger

31:07.714 --> 31:09.436
Or more gifted, hear me church.

31:09.816 --> 31:13.320
Being on mission isn't about standing up here on a platform with a microphone.

31:14.262 --> 31:16.204
Or being the most confident person in a room.

31:16.604 --> 31:18.426
The scripture says Caleb had a different what?

31:19.628 --> 31:20.969
A different spirit.

31:21.790 --> 31:26.255
Caleb had a different spirit and he followed the Lord wholeheartedly.

31:27.076 --> 31:29.900
And Caleb's faith wasn't just rewarded personally.

31:30.560 --> 31:32.983
It created inheritance for generations after him.

31:34.205 --> 31:35.506
Verse 24 again.

31:35.682 --> 31:45.958
But because my servant Caleb has a different spirit and follows me wholeheartedly, see this, I will bring him into the land he went to, and his descendants will inherit it.

31:47.280 --> 31:57.956
His obedience carved out a territory for his children, their children, and their children, who we see later in the book of Joshua, would inherit the very land those giants once lived on.

31:57.996 --> 32:00.079
How incredible is that?

32:00.099 --> 32:04.466
The same land that the voice of fear tried to warn him of,

32:04.866 --> 32:07.089
The action of faith delivered him to you.

32:08.711 --> 32:11.494
The action of faith delivered him to you.

32:12.215 --> 32:19.543
Church, could it just be that the missions we're afraid to embark on now will become the very victories we proclaim tomorrow?

32:21.826 --> 32:23.888
The salvation we never thought was possible.

32:25.390 --> 32:32.178
The shift in circumstances that neighbour or family member stood next to you in church a year from now,

32:32.930 --> 32:37.275
Those names on the prayer cards in a wholehearted relationship with Jesus.

32:37.315 --> 32:39.998
And what do we hear about Joshua?

32:41.560 --> 32:51.312
Well, in Joshua chapter three, he goes on to lead the Israelites into that very promised land that we heard about in numbers in a miraculous way that made no sense.

32:52.433 --> 32:56.818
So I think something about mission is it often requires our obedience before our understanding.

32:57.698 --> 33:01.222
Sometimes we want to know what God's doing, and we're like, Lord, what's going on?

33:01.242 --> 33:01.963
You know what's going on?

33:02.023 --> 33:02.364
Tell me.

33:02.684 --> 33:04.907
I actually think if God did show us, we wouldn't go.

33:06.429 --> 33:07.050
The tender didn't.

33:07.951 --> 33:08.732
And they saw, right?

33:09.012 --> 33:12.857
They saw the land flowing with milk and honey, and they're like, we can't do this.

33:14.118 --> 33:14.899
We can't do this.

33:16.141 --> 33:20.987
See, it didn't make sense for Joshua to lead an entire nation across a flooded river.

33:21.968 --> 33:26.674
It doesn't make sense for us to believe that an entire city can be saved by God.

33:27.490 --> 33:30.054
that we can see revival again in this generation.

33:30.114 --> 33:39.669
That you could be the very answer to your family, your neighborhood, your workplace, your school or your university.

33:39.689 --> 33:47.722
I want to share another story about being on mission and not shrinking back or perhaps shrinking back in my case.

33:47.782 --> 33:48.163
We'll see.

33:48.683 --> 33:55.474
When I was 18, I went to Bible College for two years and we used to do this thing every Tuesday where we would literally be on mission.

33:55.906 --> 34:03.775
Now, what that would look like is we'd go out into the city and we'd meet people on the streets and talk to them about Jesus.

34:04.135 --> 34:05.016
We might pray for them.

34:05.056 --> 34:06.718
We might just come alongside them.

34:06.738 --> 34:08.420
And I actually really didn't enjoy this.

34:09.021 --> 34:10.202
I found it really uncomfortable.

34:10.723 --> 34:14.507
And in my head, it was just like that thing of, you know, when you go up, someone's like, hey, can I tell you about Jesus?

34:14.928 --> 34:16.990
It's like, it's just a really weird and uncomfortable thing.

34:17.050 --> 34:22.176
But, you know, I thought, okay, God, this is your idea.

34:22.196 --> 34:23.858
This is not my idea.

34:24.290 --> 34:26.012
So I wanna work with you in this.

34:26.072 --> 34:29.997
And one morning, as I was praying, I just said, God, I'm gonna need some names.

34:31.518 --> 34:33.741
You know everyone by name, so give me them too.

34:34.482 --> 34:36.024
So I'm not just approaching strangers.

34:36.965 --> 34:41.650
And I sense the Holy Spirit say to me, you're gonna meet someone, his name begins with Jay.

34:41.670 --> 34:43.412
I thought, well, that's helpful.

34:44.774 --> 34:46.756
The name begins with Jay, okay, thank you Lord.

34:47.477 --> 34:50.681
And then I felt like he gave me the name Jake.

34:50.701 --> 34:51.602
And I was like, okay.

34:52.354 --> 34:53.115
I can work with that.

34:53.176 --> 34:53.977
That's someone's name.

34:54.037 --> 34:55.901
And off I went out on mission.

34:55.961 --> 34:59.207
And the first person I approached, they asked me if I had a cigarette.

34:59.227 --> 35:00.530
I said, no, but what I do have.

35:03.175 --> 35:06.060
I said, oh, can I just talk to you about Jesus?

35:06.902 --> 35:09.206
And he turned out to his name again with a J.

35:09.867 --> 35:11.811
And then the following person, their name began with a J.

35:11.972 --> 35:12.753
And the following person.

35:12.793 --> 35:14.336
So I thought, it's a hat trick.

35:14.556 --> 35:15.378
It was good, right?

35:16.034 --> 35:23.502
And then I still haven't met Jake, and I'd written it down in the morning, because I wanted to know that if I'd met Jake, I could show him eight o'clock this morning, I was praying for you.

35:23.542 --> 35:29.829
And as we were leaving the city, I was walking, and I just caught eyes of someone, and I was like, that's Jake.

35:30.289 --> 35:32.732
So I ran after him in the city center.

35:32.772 --> 35:34.794
I just ran, and I was like, sorry.

35:35.235 --> 35:37.817
That's gonna sound really weird, but it's your name, Jake.

35:38.158 --> 35:39.319
And he was like, yeah?

35:39.960 --> 35:41.061
And I was like, this is my moment.

35:41.081 --> 35:43.403
I was like, the Lord is real, it's real!

35:43.644 --> 35:44.625
Come on!

35:44.645 --> 35:45.746
But inside, I was like,

35:45.986 --> 35:53.156
I said, this is going to sound really weird, but I'm a Christian and I really believe that God wanted me to meet you today.

35:53.176 --> 35:57.002
He began to weep and I was like, what's going on?

35:57.022 --> 36:01.188
And he said that he was questioning life and whether he still wanted to be here.

36:02.590 --> 36:06.816
And he said, God, if you're real, I need you to reveal yourself to me today.

36:06.856 --> 36:11.282
And at that moment, yeah, please come.

36:18.658 --> 36:22.023
At that moment, I was able to pray with him there and then we were both crying at that point.

36:22.703 --> 36:24.967
And I was just like, well, God, you're so intentional.

36:25.507 --> 36:29.392
You know, sometimes we can think being on mission is a scary thing, but it's not our idea.

36:29.413 --> 36:31.575
It's his idea.

36:31.696 --> 36:36.282
Joshua and Caleb's obedience saved an entire people group.

36:36.302 --> 36:38.064
Our mission isn't just about now.

36:38.825 --> 36:39.927
It's about legacy.

36:41.188 --> 36:48.338
Your yes and my yes to the mission matters more than our comfort, more than our personal success or our moment.

36:48.962 --> 36:53.548
It's for our children, our community and the generations to come.

36:54.649 --> 36:57.493
We don't obey the mission just to enter into his promises.

36:57.873 --> 36:59.875
We obey them so that others can inherit them.

36:59.916 --> 37:02.679
Don't shrink back.

37:03.560 --> 37:06.544
Who knows what Jake had planned to do that day before that encounter?

37:07.445 --> 37:10.228
You see, history changes when someone refuses to shrink back.

37:11.530 --> 37:14.514
History changes when someone refuses to shrink back.

37:15.575 --> 37:18.098
And as I was praying for you guys in this room,

37:18.978 --> 37:23.665
And I just really felt like the Holy Spirit wanted me to pray over some groups of people.

37:23.685 --> 37:29.152
